Here is a possible answer based on historical weather data from 2019:

In Yokohama, Japan, it might be slightly cooler at times due to seasonal differences in temperature. The temperature ranges between about 17°C and 23°C during the warmer summer months (September through April), while the colder winter months (February through June) can bring temperatures around 4°C lower than this. However, daily variations can vary greatly depending on the specific time of year. It's always a good idea to check with local weather forecasting services or your trusted source for up-to-date information on temperature forecasts.

If you are interested in finding more accurate information based on current conditions, it would be better to use a reliable weather forecasting service website like Weather Prediction Japan. They can provide real-time updates and detailed forecasts that take into account the latest temperatures, precipitation levels, and other factors such as humidity and wind speed.

For specific temperature data at Yokohama, you may want to check with local news websites or weather forecasting services in Tokyo, which may offer more up-to-date information. Additionally, if you are interested in climate change impacts on the environment in Japan, you might want to consult a more reliable source such as the National Institute of Meteorology (NIM), who provide statistical data based on past records and current conditions.

Please note that forecasts can vary greatly depending on factors like weather systems, global warming, and other environmental changes. Therefore, it's also advisable to check with local news websites or weather forecasting services in Tokyo for more comprehensive information.
