On December 19th, 2018, an earthquake occurred during the morning and caused widespread damage around Okanemachi city. The first quake was a 3.1 magnitude on the Richter scale. However, after an estimated 56 seconds from the moment of occurrence to the moment of peak magnitudes, which is approximately 5.9 meters above ground level, a smaller earthquake occurred with an aftershock magnitude of 4.2, which lasted for about 30 minutes. The largest magnitude earthquake in history that affected Japan.
On February 18th, 2019, another earthquake occurred due to the aftershock of January's earthquake. The magnitude was again 5.9 meters above sea level and lasted for around 10 minutes.
Today is a day when people are able to see a beautiful sunrise in Yokohama. However, since this day is also a holiday, it is not possible to take photos or videos on the website.
